Preheat Panasonic(R) Countertop Induction Oven to Medium on the "Grill" setting. Combine cauliflower florets, olive oil, garlic salt, and pepper in a large mixing bowl; mix thoroughly. Place cauliflower florets on the grill pan and roast for 20 minutes, mixing and turning halfway. Place florets in a food processor in batches and pulse into rice-sized pieces. Cover riced cauliflower and keep warm. Preheat Panasonic(R) Countertop Induction Oven to Medium-High. Brush a thin coat of teriyaki glaze on all sides of the tofu slices and place on the grill pan. Grill slices for 1 1/2 minutes per side. Serve grilled tofu over riced cauliflower topped with desired amount of teriyaki glaze. Garnish with green onions.